article.headline: North Dakota 74, Houston Baptist 70
article.story: HOUSTON -- Troy Huff scored a career-high 31 points and Aaron Anderson buried the game-deciding 3-pointer in the final minute of overtime as North Dakota escaped with a 74-70 victory over Houston Baptist on Thursday night. Huff's biggest basket was a jumper with 14 seconds left in regulation that forced overtime. Huff had a double-double, also grabbing 12 rebounds for the Fighting Sioux (15-14, 7-4 Great West. Anderson came up huge by hitting a 3-pointer for a 71-68 lead with 46 seconds to go. He finished with 10 points. Patrick Mitchell added 12, and Jamal Webb had a career-best 11 rebounds. Andrew Gonzalez scored 19 points for the Huskies (4-24, 2-9), who have lost six of their last seven. Terry Bembry added 12 and Fred Hinnenkamp 10. Michael Moss had seven steals, extending his streak to 29 games. North Dakota outshot the Huskies 46.2 percent to 34.2 percent.
